How well, if at all, do you feel you understand each of the following? (Please select one option on each row)
LAM_Q2_1. Data protection and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)

LAM_Q3. The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is a legal framework that sets out guidelines for the collection and processing of personal information from individuals who live in the European Union (EU). 

Which, if any, of the following have ever helped inform you about data protection rights and GDPR? (Please select all that apply. If nothing in particular has helped inform you about data protection and GDPR, please select the 'Not applicable' option)
Marketing information from organisations I interact with (e.g emails, leaflets etc.)
A training course (e.g. internal or external training at work/ college etc.)
Not applicable -  nothing in particular has helped to inform me about data protection and GDPR

LAM_Q5a. For the following question by, 'personal data', we mean data that can be used to identify an individual (e.g. age, gender, address, telephone number etc.).

Which, if any, of the following would be indications to you that an organisation is using personal data that they hold about you ethically? (Please select all that apply)
Only collecting the necessary personal data to provide me with a service
Providing information about how personal data about me is used by the organisation
Providing information about who the organisation is sharing personal data about me with
Providing information about any payments that they may receive for sharing personal data about me
Providing information about assessments they carry out on their storage of personal data
Having an independent data ethics board that assesses how they use data
Asking my opinion about how they are using personal data about me
The organisation sharing personal data about me with UK government to improve public services
The organisation sharing personal data about me with charities to support their missions
The organisation sharing personal data about me with researchers to support their research

LAM_Q4. As a reminder, for the following question by, 'personal data', we mean data that can be used to identify an individual (e.g. age, gender, address, telephone number etc.). Thinking about what you view as the ethical use of data...

How important, if at all, is it to you that the organisations you interact with everyday use personal data about you ethically?

LAM_Q8a. Please imagine that you and your family were able to receive a personalised public service (such as social care or education) if you shared personal data about you with your local authority...

In general, which, if any, of the following types of data would you be comfortable sharing with your local authority in exchange for this type of service? (Please select all that apply)
Personal data about me (e.g. my name and address etc.)
Sensitive data about me (e.g. my race or sexual orientation etc.)
Behavioural data about me (e.g. what I like on social media or my travel patterns etc.)
Data about my community (e.g. statistics about the kind of people who live in my area or where crimes happen etc.)
Data about my environment (e.g. air quality or bus routes etc.)

LAM_Q9. Please imagine that your local authority was able to improve how they deliver public services (such as social care or education) by collecting data which was not used to pinpoint or target individuals...

In general, which, if any, of the following kinds of data would you be comfortable with your local authority collecting from you? (Please select all that apply)
Data from surveys that ask questions about my preferences
Data from surveys that ask questions about my habits such as how long it takes me to travel to work
Data from surveys that ask questions about my sensitive personal characteristics such as my race or sexual orientation
What I am saying on social media
What I am searching for online
How I am using online services provided by the local authority
How I am using non-government services (e.g. Uber, AirBnB etc.)
The movements of my mobile phone
Videos of me from CCTV cameras
Air quality from sensors in my area
Pictures of vehicle licence plates from traffic cameras
